Successful access refers to instances where the user is authorized to access the register, as indicated by the is_authorized flag being set to 1; 
Frequently accessed registers are those with at least one access event; 
Authorized access refers to access events where is_authorized is 1; 
Descending order by the date of the most recent access refers to the latest access dates appearing first.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS default_register_value_count
FROM register_versions
WHERE is_default = 1;

SELECT description
FROM register_types
WHERE is_deprecated = 0;
